name: Battle of Moscow - Test 1.1.1
description: September 30, 1941. Operation "Typhoon" has begun. German tank spearheads are ready to break through the Soviet defenses and encircle them. But their resistance is fierce, while Soviets build fortifications and gather reinforcements. Will Moscow fall?

value.title: Moscow Militia Divisions
value.message: On October 11th, after accelerated training, four Militia divisions were formed in Moscow.

value.title: Defence of Kalinin!
value.message: The city of Kalinin (currently - Tver') is a major hub on the railway Moscow-Leningrad (currently - St. Petersburg). To prevent the Germans from capturing Kalinin, the 5th Rifle Division was transferred from the reserve of Stavka to the city. Vatutin's task force, formed from reserve units of the Northwestern Front, soon arrived in the Torzhok area. Furthermore, a people's militia, reinforced by cadets, was urgently formed in the city itself.

value.title: Breakthrough in the South!
value.message: On October 3, the German 2nd Tank Group succeeded in making a major breakthrough on the southern flank of the Bryansk Front. After advancing hundreds of kilometers, the 4th Panzer Division managed to capture the city of Oryol completely defenceless.

value.title: Guderian Exploits the Breakthrough!
value.message: After successful capture of the city of Oryol, H. Guderian, commander of the 2nd Tank Group, reinforced the resulting breakthrough by sending three Panzer and one motorized division.

value.title: The Soviet Response to the Breakthrough
value.message: After the capture of the city of Oryol by Germans, the road to Tula and Moscow was practically unguarded. Stavka urgently deployed from reserves two Tank Brigades, 1st Rifle Corps and 5th Airborne Corps in the Mtsensk area.

value.title: G. Zhukov Arrives!
value.message: After the disaster at Vyazma, J. Stalin ordered the recall of G. Zhukov from Leningrad (currently St. Petersburg) to organize the defense of Moscow as quickly as possible. Zhukov's first decision was to deploy the few recently replenished divisions on the southwestern approaches to Moscow.

value.title: Defence of Tula!
value.message: Tula, the City of Gunsmiths, is a key industrial center and logistics hub on the southern approaches to Moscow. To prevent its capture by Guderian's Panzer Group, Stavka transferred the 260th Rifle Division to the city. Furthermore, the Tula Workers' Regiment was urgently created in the city, reinforced by the 156th NKVD Regiment and local police forces.

value.title: Divisions from the Far East arrive  at Tula!
value.message: To reinforce the defence of the key city of Tula and its eastern approaches, Stavka decided to send arriving from the Far East 239th and 413th Rifle Divisions to Tula and Stalinogorsk.

value.title: Soviet Tank Wave!
value.message: By the end of October 1941, despite a severe shortage of tanks, the Soviet command had formed or replenished up to 30 tank brigades. These units were armed with the latest T-34 and KV tanks. A significant portion of the new tank units were formed near Moscow and immediately sent to the front.

value.title: Soviet Counteroffensive in the North!
value.message: By the end of November 1941, the Soviet command was concentrating troops of the newly formed 20th Army and the 1st Shock Army in the Zagorsk (now Sergiev Posad) area. Stavka planned to launch these armies into a counteroffensive north of Moscow in early December. However, the German breakthrough near Yakhroma forced the immediate deployment of the 1st Shock Army to eliminate the breakthrough.

value.title: Soviet Reinforcements in the South-East!
value.message: By the end of November 1941, the Soviet command had formed 13 rifle and 4 cavalry divisions in the Volga Military District. They took part in the Red Army's winter counteroffensive on the southern flank of the Western Front.

value.title: The Current Situation on the Eastern Front
value.message:
Despite the stunning successes of the first months of the war, the pace of the German advance in the central sector slowed significantly, and losses were unexpectedly high. Near Smolensk, the Germans were forced to go on the defensive for a time. However, by constantly counterattacking and pinning down the enemy, the Red Army also suffered huge losses.

On September 30, the Wehrmacht will launch Operation Typhoon, its General Offensive on Moscow. Powerful tank forces are once again preparing to break through the Soviet defenses and encircle them. But although the Wehrmacht outnumbers the Red Army, German supply lines are already severely stretched, and operational reserves are depleted reinforcements are not expected.

The Soviet command is busily forming new divisions. The front-line units simply need to hold out until they arrive.

The German command needs to capture Moscow in 50 moves, while the Soviet command must hold the city at any cost.

value.title: The Fall of Moscow!
value.message: Despite desperate resistance, Moscow fell under the decisive blow of German troops! The Soviet Union's most important political, industrial, and logistical center lies in German hands. The morale of the Soviet troops was completely undermined, and all attempts by Soviet counterattacks on the city were repelled.

value.title: Soviet Victory in the Battle of Moscow!
value.message: Despite the catastrophes of the first months of the war and countless losses, the Red Army was able to defend Moscow and repel the German offensive. The German strategy of blitzkrieg was thwarted  however, a significant portion of the USSR is still under German control, and complete victory in the war has not yet been achieved.
